#uint8 used from stackOverFlow
#https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49643907/clipping-input-data-to-the-valid-range-for-imshow-with-rgb-data-0-1-for-floa

def plotcluster(X,imshape, clusterLabels, c):
    plt.suptitle('cluster' + str(c))
    plt.figure(figsize = (10,10)) 
    Xcl = X[clusterLabels == c]
    

    inds = np.random.choice(len(Xcl), 6, replace = False)
    for i, ind in enumerate(inds):
        ax = plt.subplot(2,3, i+1)
        array = Xcl[ind,:].reshape(imshape) 
        ax.imshow(array.astype("uint8"))
        ax.axis("off")

    plt.show()
In [42]:

Observation & Results¶

  • Using k = 5, there wasnt really much difference in image output as they both outputted alot of bar graphs. There is also an instance of lack in background color

  • usingk = 3 and k = 4, There was more variability in images which showcase line plots,pie charts, scatterplots, etc. There is also an instance where these k's provided background color in their visuals

  • With a bigger sample size there seems to be more related plots together such as where k = 5 which most of the plots were bar plots

  • With more clusters, the more resolutions appear on the visuals leading to a clearer and bigger image

  • The clusters contain vast imagery of visualizations that come in different forms of language and industry decisions

3.2 Get this code to work with your image and understand what it does. Explain:¶

(a) (0.4 point) What does the shape of pixels mean?

  • Answer: The dimensionality. 
      -Pixels in the code
  -Its a tuple that uses height, width, and channels (Number of color channels used) in that order

(b) (0.4 point) What is matrix M? Why does it have 671,040 rows and 3 columns in this example?

  • Answer: It represents the 2D version of my image that was originally in 3D

  • Matrix M reconfigures the image into multiplying height and width into 1 column and the other as a color channel (height * width, color channel)

    • 699 x 960 = 671,040
  • The 3 columns are the RBG values

(c) (0.4 point) What do cl values tell us? E.g. if cl[12345] = 2, what does it mean?

  • Answer: Its the application of Kmeans assigning clusters to every pixel individually
  • cl[12345] = 2 represents the cluster assignment label when Kmeans was applied

(d) (0.4 point) What are the columns of center color values printed above? E.g. the first row, second column is value 163.37. What does that number mean?

  • Answer: The columns of the center color values represent the average color schemes of R,G,B for each cluster which helps reconfigure my images color-code into reduced color schemes from the averages of colors used
  • The value 163.37 comes from the average color of green within the 1st cluster(row)

(e) (0.4 point) How many center color values are there? Why do we have this number?

  • Answer: The amount of center color values is represented by the amount I designated in my Kmeans model which is ---> 16

  • We have this number for color optimization purposes to illuminate for processing using the color average on each pexil for each respective cluster

  • Since we reduced our image to smaller 16 colors are the images we reduced to

3.3 Next repeat the above by reducing the number of colors to 2, and 4. Show the pictures!¶

In [53]:
def imageRevise(imageLocation, colorCount):
    pixels = imread(imageLocation)
    M = pixels.reshape((-1, pixels.shape[2]))
    m = KMeans(n_clusters = colorCount).fit(M)
    c1 = m.predict(M)
    centers = m.cluster_centers_
    compressed = centers[c1] / 255
    compressed = compressed.reshape(pixels.shape)
    ax = plt.axes()
    ax.set_aspect("equal")
    _ = plt.imshow(compressed)
    _ = plt.show()
